en_115838_0	Sri Lanka Freedom Party will celebrate its 64th anniversary in Polonnaruwa today under the patronage of party leader, President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_115838_1	Former SLFP leaders, including former Presidents Mahinda Rajapaksa and Chandrika Bandaranaike Kumaratunga have been invited.
en_115838_2	SLFP was founded by the 4th Prime Minister of Sri Lanka late S.W.R.D Bandaranaike in 1951 and, since then, it has been one of the two largest parties in the Sri Lankan political arena.
en_115838_3	An Ashirvada Pooja will be held at the ancient Somawathiya Temple from 7 a.m. on September 2 to invoke blessings on the party.
en_115838_4	Multi-faith religious ceremonies will be held throughout the week at places of religious worship to invoke blessings on the party, the people and the country.
